<div class="article-single">
<main id="content" class="article-single__view">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
<article class="article-single__wrap">
<header class="article-single-intro">
<div class="article-single-intro__wrap is-schar-safe">
<div class="article-single-intro__post-info"><p class="article-single-intro__category"><a href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/" class="article-single-intro__cat-link">Planning &amp; Workflow for Podcasting</a></p></div>
<h1 class="singular-post-intro__headline">How Does Podcasting, Blogging &#038; Video Work Together? Content Stacking</h1>
<div class="article-single-intro__thumb-wrap">
<div class="article-single-intro__thumb-responsive-wrap" style="padding-bottom:56.25%;">
<img src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1.jpg" alt="article featured image" class="article-single-intro__post-thumb tph-skip-lazyload" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 350px, (min-width: 992px) 290px, (min-width: 768px) 270px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-290x163.jpg 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-350x197.jpg 350w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-445x250.jpg 445w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-635x357.jpg 635w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-580x326.jpg 580w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-700x394.jpg 700w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-890x501.jpg 890w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1-1270x714.jpg 1270w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Content_Stacking-1.jpg 1280w" width="1280" height="720">
</div>
</div>
</div>
<time datetime="2021-08-31T08:00:00+01:00" class="screen-reader-text">Tue, 31 Aug 2021 08:00:00 +0100</time>
</header>
<div class="article-single__content">
<div class="tph-post-content is-schar-safe">
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
<html><body><p><em>This is the first chapter in our <strong>Content Stacking</strong> series, all about producing prolific levels of content.</em></p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-full-content-stacking-series-guide-index">Full Content Stacking Series Guide Index</h3>
<ul>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36461" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/content-stacking-series/">How Does Podcasting, Blogging &amp; Video Work Together?</a>&nbsp;#1</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36462" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/finding-content-ideas/">Finding Content Ideas &amp; Getting the Most From Every One</a>&nbsp;#2</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36463" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/content-structure/">A Podcast Structure for the Most Effective Teaching Possible&nbsp;</a>#3</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36464" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/scripting-presenting-content-prolific-repurposing/">Scripting &amp; Presenting Content for Prolific Re-purposing&nbsp;</a>#4</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36465" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/3-step-content-editing-process-create-spectacular-clarity/">The 3-Step Content Editing Process to Create Spectacular Clarity</a>&nbsp;#5</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36466" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/how-to-write-a-blog-for-prolific-repurposing/">How to Write a Blog for Prolific Repurposing</a>&nbsp;#6</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36467" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/recording-audio-video-for-prolific-repurposing/">Recording Audio &amp; Video for Prolific Repurposing</a>&nbsp;#7</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36468" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/blog-grow-podcast-video/">Blog Posts that Grow Podcast Listeners &amp; Video Viewers</a>&nbsp;#8</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36469" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/youtube-videos-that-drive-action-promote-podcast/">YouTube Videos that Drive Action &amp; Promote Your Podcast</a>&nbsp;#9</li>
<li><a data-lasso-id="36470" href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/planning/how-to-drive-action-from-a-podcast/">How to Drive Action From a Podcast</a>&nbsp;#10</li>
</ul>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-css-opacity">
<p>In this series, I want to show you how to make regular content easier, while still keeping the quality sky-high. It means squeezing the most juice possible from every single content idea you have. You do that by putting just a bit more thought into how to plan, produce and publish.</p>
<p>Interested? Alrighty, let&rsquo;s have a look at <strong>Content Stacking</strong>.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-podcasting-sits-amongst-the-content-stacking-mix">How Podcasting Sits Amongst the Content Stacking Mix</h2>
<p>Podcasting is what I do. It&rsquo;s the medium I love, both to consume and to create. I work every day with people who are starting shows, improving their content, growing an audience and moulding fans. That&rsquo;s the goal, in the end: creating fans. Of your brand. Of your product. Of YOU.</p>
<p>Podcasting is still, for me, the most effective way to create fans. I&rsquo;ll go through the options to show you why.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-text-equals-reach">Text Equals Reach</h3>
<p>Text is great, to begin with. It&rsquo;s low barrier, high reach, completely ubiquitous. &nbsp;It can deliver quick value hits as easily as long, deep explorations of your subject. It should always be part of your content mix and forms the front line of your awareness efforts. But&hellip; when it comes to building rapport, and deeper relationships, it can&rsquo;t quite compete with rich media.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-media-equals-engagement">Media Equals Engagement</h3>
<p>Media can captivate through personality, values, and honesty, all of which are delivered in spades when we see or hear someone speak. Video and audio show the real you, creating a personal connection that only the best writers can replicate.</p>
<p>But, video has one weakness; the goldfish brain. Time and again, stats show the ideal video length is <a href="https://biteable.com/blog/youtube-analytics-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">sub-5 minutes</a>. It&rsquo;s a weakness that the written word shares, resulting in a generation of skim-readers. </p>
<p>The reason is simple: both text and video are asking for one of the most valuable things we can offer: our time. And, not only our time, but our attention. Our <em>full</em> attention, for as long as it takes.</p>
<p>It turns out that our attention is precious, and we&rsquo;ll not give it for long without damn good reason. Enter the Podcast.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-audio-equals-trust">Audio Equals Trust</h3>
<div class="wp-block-image alignright size-full">
<figure class><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="420" height="517" alt="text, media, and audio = attention and trust" data-srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path.jpg 420w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path-244x300.jpg 244w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path-290x357.jpg 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path-350x431.jpg 350w" data-src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path.jpg" data-sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 635px, (min-width: 992px) 570px, (min-width: 768px) 650px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="wp-image-1959 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw=="><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="420" height="517" src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path.jpg" alt="text, media, and audio = attention and trust" class="wp-image-1959" srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path.jpg 420w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path-244x300.jpg 244w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path-290x357.jpg 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/content-stacking-engagement-path-350x431.jpg 350w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 635px, (min-width: 992px) 570px, (min-width: 768px) 650px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)"></noscript></figure></div>
<p>The podcast is less selfish, more easy-going. It&rsquo;s not looking for our full attention, just a smidge will do. You can listen in those moments when you&rsquo;re performing by habit, like driving to work, walking the dog, or cooking your dinner. &nbsp;</p>
<p>It turns out, by being a little less selfish, the Podcast attention span skyrockets. <a href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/listening/podcast-industry-stats/" data-lasso-id="32733">Some of the most popular shows in the world run for an hour or more</a>, and still generate millions of listeners. At the extreme end of the scale, Dan Carlin commands 6 figure audiences, keeping listeners entranced for up to 3 hours an episode, entirely solo!</p>
<p>So, video <em>and</em> podcasting allow your audience to know you, putting out the real you. Both have a real power to create that connection. But, Podcasting, through this massive attention, has the capability to do this on a huge scale, engaging listeners perhaps for hours at a time.&nbsp;That&rsquo;s what creates a personal connection, generates trust and starts to nurture fanatical fans. And that&rsquo;s why I think every content creator should have a podcast.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-simple-let-s-go-all-in-on-podcasting-no">Simple: Let&rsquo;s Go &ldquo;All-In&rdquo; on Podcasting. No?</h2>
<p>No.</p>
<p>As much as I&rsquo;d like to say it, Podcasting isn&rsquo;t a panacea. I&rsquo;m the first to admit it works most effectively alongside its media siblings: text and video. There&rsquo;s more than one reason for this, but the big one is that which we all crave and fear in equal measure. Google search.</p>
<p>When it comes to search, <a href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/promotion/podcast-discoverability/" data-lasso-id="32734">Podcasting doesn&rsquo;t (yet) have a big enough mouth</a>. Strange, given that there&rsquo;s are no shortage of&nbsp;big-mouths stinking up the digital airwaves. But, here we&rsquo;re talking about the mouth of your funnel. Your sales funnel, to be exact.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-what-s-a-funnel">What&rsquo;s a Funnel?</h2>
<p>A sales funnel is so-called because your sales process is shaped like a funnel. You put &lsquo;leads&rsquo; in the top of the funnel. It&rsquo;s widest there &ndash; that&rsquo;s the size of your mouth, or the number of people in that point of the funnel &ndash; because it&rsquo;s the first contact people have with you. At this point there&rsquo;s no commitment, so you get lots of people (leads, if we&rsquo;re being mercenary about it) dropping in for a look. That might just be a simple search visitor, at the very top of the funnel.</p>
<div class="wp-block-image alignright size-full is-resized">
<figure class><img decoding="async" alt="Content stacking marketing funnel" width="400" data-srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel.png 1000w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-300x300.png 300w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-150x150.png 150w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-768x768.png 768w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-290x290.png 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-350x350.png 350w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-445x445.png 445w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-635x635.png 635w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-580x580.png 580w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-700x700.png 700w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-890x890.png 890w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-72x72.png 72w" data-src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel.png" data-sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 635px, (min-width: 992px) 570px, (min-width: 768px) 650px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="wp-image-1960 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw=="><noscript><img decoding="async" src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel.png" alt="Content stacking marketing funnel" class="wp-image-1960" width="400" srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel.png 1000w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-300x300.png 300w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-150x150.png 150w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-768x768.png 768w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-290x290.png 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-350x350.png 350w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-445x445.png 445w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-635x635.png 635w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-580x580.png 580w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-700x700.png 700w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-890x890.png 890w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Marketing_Funnel-72x72.png 72w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 635px, (min-width: 992px) 570px, (min-width: 768px) 650px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)"></noscript></figure></div>
<p>Go down the funnel, though, and people are making more commitment: they decide to read another article, watch a video, subscribe to your email course, buy a product. As this happens, they move from awareness to consideration to conversion. That might be a purchase, or <a href="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/promotion/email-marketing-for-podcasters/" data-lasso-id="32735">subscribing to your email list</a>. Then your content continues to move people through the funnel to loyalty and advocacy.</p>
<p>As you move through this process &ndash; down the funnel &ndash; you whittle down the number of people, because a few prospects drop out at each stage. That&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s a &lsquo;funnel&rsquo; &ndash; it gets narrower as you work your way down.</p>
<p>One aim of your business is to maximise the &lsquo;mouth&rsquo; of your funnel, by which I mean the number of people entering it at the top(quality matters too, but we&rsquo;re taking relevant, good quality content as a given). And one way of maximising that &lsquo;mouth&rsquo;, is simply to attract more traffic to your content.</p>
<p>That&rsquo;s where Podcasting needs help. The public&nbsp;<em>can</em>&nbsp;make first contact with you via your Podcast, but podcast search traffic is minute compared to Google or YouTube. Google has the biggest mouth there is, and YouTube is not far behind. That means you need text to maximise your reach, video to supplement it and then podcasting to create your fans. Here&rsquo;s how that works.</p>
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="576" alt="funnel of coffee beans" data-srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-300x169.jpeg 300w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-290x163.jpeg 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-350x197.jpeg 350w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-445x250.jpeg 445w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-635x357.jpeg 635w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-580x326.jpeg 580w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-700x394.jpeg 700w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-890x501.jpeg 890w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-1270x714.jpeg 1270w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works.jpeg 1280w" data-src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-1024x576.jpeg" data-sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 635px, (min-width: 992px) 570px, (min-width: 768px) 650px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="wp-image-25501 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw=="><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="576" src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-1024x576.jpeg" alt="funnel of coffee beans" class="wp-image-25501" srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-300x169.jpeg 300w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-290x163.jpeg 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-350x197.jpeg 350w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-445x250.jpeg 445w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-635x357.jpeg 635w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-580x326.jpeg 580w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-700x394.jpeg 700w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-890x501.jpeg 890w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works-1270x714.jpeg 1270w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/why_a_funnel_works.jpeg 1280w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 635px, (min-width: 992px) 570px, (min-width: 768px) 650px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)"></noscript></figure>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-the-content-stack-using-the-strength-of-each-medium">The Content Stack: Using the Strength of Each Medium</h2>
<p>So, we have &lsquo;leads&rsquo; at the top of the funnel, attracting as many people as we can through a mix of text, video and audio. What next? How do we then turn them into these fabled fanatical fans? That&rsquo;s where the content stack comes in.</p>
<p>Basic principles: the public&nbsp;types a question into Google, you write a blog post to answer it. That&rsquo;s the biggest reach you have: text search.</p>
<p>Next, you raise the likability, the credibility, <em>the trust</em> by introducing personality. We talked already about how both video and podcasting are great for this, but video has the reach advantage. The audience is huge for video search, and it&rsquo;s so quick and easy to watch a few good video clips. Search, watch, search, watch. Simple, no tech involved. That&rsquo;s great &ndash; it shows people who you are,&nbsp;and&nbsp;encourages them to make a bigger commitment, which is to listen to your podcast.</p>
<p>Podcasting is where you build a really personal connection, absolutely maximising that trust. It includes the personality &ndash; same as video &ndash; but I talked already about the&nbsp;force multiplier:&nbsp;attention.</p>
<p>Every minute they listen to your show, you&rsquo;re nurturing their&nbsp;trust, and because you have them for so long each week, you&rsquo;re doing it&nbsp;fast! Not to repeat myself&hellip; well, actually, to repeat myself entirely, <em>that&rsquo;s</em>&nbsp;what creates fanatical fans, and&nbsp;<em>that&rsquo;s</em>&nbsp;what makes it worth guiding them through to a podcast.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-so-write-film-and-record">So, Write, Film AND Record&hellip;.?</h2>
<div class="wp-block-image alignright size-full is-resized">
<figure class><img decoding="async" alt="the content stacking model" width="400" data-srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration.png 985w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-300x274.png 300w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-768x702.png 768w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-290x265.png 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-350x320.png 350w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-445x407.png 445w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-635x580.png 635w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-580x530.png 580w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-700x640.png 700w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-890x813.png 890w" data-src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration.png" data-sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 635px, (min-width: 992px) 570px, (min-width: 768px) 650px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="wp-image-1961 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw=="><noscript><img decoding="async" src="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration.png" alt="the content stacking model" class="wp-image-1961" width="400" srcset="https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration.png 985w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-300x274.png 300w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-768x702.png 768w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-290x265.png 290w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-350x320.png 350w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-445x407.png 445w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-635x580.png 635w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-580x530.png 580w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-700x640.png 700w, https://www.thepodcasthost.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The_content_stack-illustration-890x813.png 890w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 635px, (min-width: 992px) 570px, (min-width: 768px) 650px, (min-width: 576px) 510px, calc(100vw - 30px)"></noscript></figure></div>
<p>Yes. Do it all. That&rsquo;s how you&rsquo;re going to create fanatical fans, stand out in your market and beat your competitors.</p>
<p>I&rsquo;ve been working on ways to break it down, to systematise it and to output prolific levels of content, all while still doing your real job and retaining creativity. That&rsquo;s the model I&rsquo;ll cover in the rest of this series.</p>
<p>The key here is finding that model that makes sure you get the maximum you can out of every bit of content you produce. Not to mention planning it so that every bit of content works together, drawing people through the mediums.</p>
<p>Everything they consume stacks up in front of them, and every block of media in that stack is another chunk of engagement with your brand. Once they&rsquo;ve stacked up enough views, enough reads, enough listens, that&rsquo;s when they become fans. And that&rsquo;s when they buy with you, and promote you to their friends.</p>
<p>I hope that&rsquo;s given a good picture of what we&rsquo;re looking to achieve here. If you&rsquo;re up for it, for building your own stack, let&rsquo;s dig in!</p>
